<div class="modal fade" id="successModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
        <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel"><%= @gemifier.repo.name %> was successfully created!</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        You can find <%= @gem_name %> on Github at <%= link_to @gemifier.repo.html_url, @gemifier.repo.html_url %>. To get started using <%= @gem_name %>, just type:
        </br>
        </br>
          <code> git clone <%= @gemifier.repo.html_url %>.git </code>
          </br>
          <code> cd <%= @gemifier.repo.name %> </code>
          </br>
          <code> sudo gem install <%= @gemifier.gem_file_name %> </code>
        </br>
        </br>
        This will install <%= @gem_name %>, giving you access to both its command line runner (just type <%= @gem_name %> in your Terminal) and the ability to require it within your Ruby applications.
        </br>
        <h5>Command Line</h5>
        Just type <code> <%= @gem_name.gem_file_name %></code>.
        </br>
        <h5>Ruby</h5>
        To require <%= @gem_name %> in a Ruby application, use:
        </br>
        <code> gem '<%= @gem_name %>', :git => '<%= @gemifier.repo.git_url %>' </code>
        </br>
        Instantiate <%= @gem_name %> by calling <code> <%= @gem_name.titleize %>::Magic.new.call</code>. Save that instance in a variable and call any of your defined methods (<code><%= @method_names.join(", ") %></code>) on it.
        </br>
        </br>
        Want to do learn more about gems? Find out how to share your gem with the Ruby community by publishing to <%= link_to 'RubyGems', 'http://guides.rubygems.org/publishing/' %> and how to <%= link_to 'create your own gem from scratch', 'http://guides.rubygems.org/publishing/' %>.
      </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-grey btn-lg btn-block" id="close-modal" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>